=====================================================================
Started/closed: 2026-06-02 (same session)
Base: nexgen=7276f53 (post-C14 merge of PR #18)

Outcome: GREEN. 55/55 tests across the codegen family + cli (bucket 7
         + projection 26 + pipeline 15 + cli 7). Was 48; +7 new in
         op-cli. Binary verified hands-on against the rails_mini
         fixture (stdout = SurrealQL DDL, exit codes 0/1/2 correct).

What landed:
  crates/op-cli/
    - Cargo.toml: declares [lib] name = op_cli AND a [[bin]] target
      `op-codegen` -> src/main.rs. Adds the op-codegen-pipeline dep.
      Keeps the pre-existing op-core dep untouched.
    - src/lib.rs (was a stub):
      * pub enum CliError { Usage(String), PathNotFound(String) }
        with Display + Error
      * pub const EXIT_USAGE = 2, EXIT_IO = 1, USAGE = "usage: ..."
      * pub fn run_codegen(rails_root: &Path) -> Result<String, CliError>
        - composes extract_core_triples + render_surreal_from_ruff
        - returns Err(PathNotFound) if path is not a directory
      * pub fn dispatch_codegen(argv: &[String]) -> Result<String, CliError>
        - exact-one-arg parser; -h / --help yield Usage; too-many-args
          yield Usage with an "(N given)" tail
    - src/main.rs (new):
      * thin shell: skip argv[0], call dispatch_codegen, print/eprintln
        + ExitCode::from(EXIT_USAGE | EXIT_IO) on errors
    - tests/cli_smoke.rs (new):
      * 7 tests covering run_codegen happy path, run_codegen IO errors
        (nonexistent, file-not-dir), dispatch (no args, -h, --help,
        too many, valid)

The shared fixture trick:
  op-cli's tests reference the rails_mini fixture from the pipeline
  crate via CARGO_MANIFEST_DIR + ../op-codegen-pipeline/tests/fixtures
  to avoid duplication. Both crates' e2e expectations stay pinned to
  the same source of truth.

End-to-end behaviour (verified hands-on):
  $ target/debug/op-codegen
  usage: op-codegen <rails-app-path>            # stderr
  $? -> 2

  $ target/debug/op-codegen /nonexistent
